  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "It can sometimes be challenging to distinguish between genuine interest and someone who might be using you. Here are some signs that can help you determine a guy's intentions:\n\n1. **Consistent Communication**: If he regularly checks in, initiates conversations, and responds promptly, it might indicate genuine interest.\n\n2. **Interest in Your Life**: A guy who likes you will be curious about your life, interests, and aspirations. He'll ask questions and remember details about you.\n\n3. **Effort Towards Plans**: Someone interested will make an effort to spend quality time with you, planning dates or outings rather than just casual 'hangouts.'\n\n4. **Emotional Support**: He offers support and is there for you during tough times, showing that he cares about your wellbeing.\n\n5. **Introduces You to Friends/Family**: If he includes you in his life by introducing you to his friends and family, it can be a strong indication of his genuine interest.\n\n6. **Respect for Boundaries**: He respects your boundaries and doesn\u2019t pressure you into doing things you\u2019re not comfortable with.\n\n7. **Physical Affection without Expectation**: If he\u2019s affectionate without always expecting something physical in return, it\u2019s a good sign.\n\n8. **Talks about the Future**: If he discusses future plans or expresses a desire for a relationship beyond the present context, especially involving you, that's usually a positive sign.\n\n9. **Equality and Balance**: He makes sure there's a balance in your interactions, not always taking or expecting more than he gives.\n\nSigns he might just be using you:\n\n1. **Inconsistent Communication**: He only reaches out when it's convenient for him, or primarily for physical reasons.\n\n2. **Lack of Personal Interest**: He seems uninterested in your life, goals, or feelings.\n\n3. **Unwillingness to Commit**: He avoids discussing the future or is reluctant to label your relationship.\n\n4. **Focus on Physical Aspects**: Interaction is primarily physical, with little emphasis on emotional connection.\n\n5. **Limited Availability**: He\u2019s frequently unavailable or disappears for days without explanation.\n\n6. **Self-Centered Conversations**: Conversations tend to revolve around him and his needs.\n\nIf you\u2019re uncertain, the best approach is open communication. Discuss your feelings and intentions with him to gain clarity and address any concerns.",
